# Git submodule prevention
# If a directory has its own .git, it should be a proper submodule listed in .gitmodules
# This prevents accidental submodule creation when copying git repositories
# **/.git/ would ignore all .git directories, but we only want to prevent accidental ones
# Instead, rely on: check for .git before adding new directories